To use this project, download the dataset from Kaggle at https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/hphphp123321/tenhou-4-player-riichi-mahjong-dataset.
After signing in, click the Download button and extract the ZIP file. 
Inside, youâ€™ll find the large SQLite database called datasets_positive.db, which contains all of the Mahjong game states used in this project. 
Once extracted, place the file in your project folder and the notebook will be able to load it directly for preprocessing and model training.
